frameDefinitions: Words in this frame describe the status of an Action with respect to a Code of laws or rules.
A Speaker expresses through language his wish to get the Addressee to act.
In this frame, an Authority allows a Protagonist to know (in some way) that they may or may not engage in an Action.
A Behavior is classified as entrenched for a Protagonist or a Society.
A Duty is imposed on a Responsible_party according to a Principle which regulates how the Responsible_party should respond to a Situation.
Under some Condition, usually left implicit, a Duty needs to be fulfilled by a  Responsible_party.
frameExamples: <t>Illegal</t> drug use is on the rise.
You think I <t>talked</t> Peter into giving me those earrings, don't you?
The police officer <t>forbid</t> me from turning around .
They escaped total Soviet invasion and occupation only by entering into a separate agreement that <t>obligated</t> them to military action against the retreating German armies.
It would <t>behoove</t> us to comprehend and personalize what Jesus had to tell his disciples
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Action</fen> is the behavior which complies with or violates the <fen>Code</fen>.
The <fen>Object</fen> complies with or violates the <fen>Code</fen> by virtue of its existence, location or possession.
The <fen>Speaker</fen> intends through the use of language to get another person to act.
The wish for action on the <fen>Addressee</fen>'s part  that the <fen>Speaker</fen> expresses.
The person that the Speaker seeks to influence to act.
The location where the <fen>Speaker</fen> talks the <fen>Addressee</fen> into performing the <fen>Content</fen>.
The <fen>Authority</fen> orders the <fen>Protagonist</fen> to not engage in a particular <fen>Action</fen>.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> wants to engage in an <fen>Action</fen>, but is ordered not to by the <fen>Authority</fen>.
The <fen>Action</fen> is what the <fen>Protagonist</fen> seeks to do, but is ordered not to.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the denying of permission occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the denial of permission occurs.
This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate the entrenched <fen>Behavior</fen>.
This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate whose entrenched <fen>Behavior</fen> is at issue.
This role marks expressions that indicate a region where the <fen>Behavior</fen> is  entrenched.
The person who must perform the <fen>Duty</fen>.
The action that the <fen>Responsible_party</fen> is obligated to perform.
The <fen>Obligator</fen> is the person who imposes the <fen>Duty</fen> on the <fen>Responsible_party</fen>.
A state of affairs that results in the <fen>Responsible_party</fen> being obligated to carry out the <fen>Duty</fen> in accordance with the <fen>Principle</fen>.
A regulating idea  (which may be instantiated as a document)  that the <fen>Responsible_party</fen> is subject to.
The time interval during which  the <fen>Duty</fen> is imposed on the <fen>Responsible_party</fen>  by the <fen>Obligator</fen> or the <fen>Situation</fen>.
A location in which the <fen>Responsible_party</fen> has a specified <fen>Duty</fen> .
The action that the <fen>Responsible_party</fen> is obligated to perform.
The person who must perform the <fen>Duty</fen>.
The time interval during which the <fen>Duty</fen> is mandatory.
A location in which the <fen>Duty</fen>  obtains.
